32// Struct that we pass to the decoder per frame to decode. We receive it again
33// in the decoder callback.
34struct RTCFrameDecodeParams {
35 RTCFrameDecodeParams(RTCVideoDecoderCallback cb, int64_t ts) : callback(cb), timestamp(ts) {}
36 RTCVideoDecoderCallback callback;
37 int64_t timestamp;
38};
39
40@interface RTCVideoDecoderH264 ()
41- (void)setError:(OSStatus)error;
42@end
43
44// This is the callback function that VideoToolbox calls when decode is
45// complete.
46void decompressionOutputCallback(void *decoderRef,
47 void *params,
48 OSStatus status,
49 VTDecodeInfoFlags infoFlags,
50 CVImageBufferRef imageBuffer,
51 CMTime timestamp,
52 CMTime duration) {
53 if (status != noErr || !imageBuffer) {
54 RTCVideoDecoderH264 *decoder = (__bridge RTCVideoDecoderH264 *)decoderRef;
55 [decoder setError:status != noErr ? status : 1];
56 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to decode frame. Status: " << status;
57 return;
58 }
59
60 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameDecodeParams> decodeParams(reinterpret_cast<RTCFrameDecodeParams *>(params));
61 // TODO(tkchin): Handle CVO properly.
62 RTCCVPixelBuffer *frameBuffer = [[RTCCVPixelBuffer alloc] initWithPixelBuffer:imageBuffer];
63 RTCVideoFrame *decodedFrame =
64 [[RTCVideoFrame alloc] initWithBuffer:frameBuffer
65 rotation:RTCVideoRotation_0
66 timeStampNs:CMTimeGetSeconds(timestamp) * rtc::kNumNanosecsPerSec];
67 decodedFrame.timeStamp = decodeParams->timestamp;
68 decodeParams->callback(decodedFrame);
69}
70
71// Decoder.
72@implementation RTCVideoDecoderH264 {
73 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef _videoFormat;
74 CMMemoryPoolRef _memoryPool;
75 VTDecompressionSessionRef _decompressionSession;
76 RTCVideoDecoderCallback _callback;
77 OSStatus _error;
78}
79
80- (instancetype)init {
81 self = [super init];
82 if (self) {
83 _memoryPool = CMMemoryPoolCreate(nil);
84 }
85 return self;
86}
87
88- (void)dealloc {
89 CMMemoryPoolInvalidate(_memoryPool);
90 CFRelease(_memoryPool);
91 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
92 [self setVideoFormat:nullptr];
93}
94
95- (NSInteger)startDecodeWithNumberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores {
96 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
97}
98
99- (NSInteger)decode:(RTCEncodedImage *)inputImage
100 missingFrames:(BOOL)missingFrames
101 codecSpecificInfo:(nullable id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)info
102 renderTimeMs:(int64_t)renderTimeMs {
103 RTC_DCHECK(inputImage.buffer);
104
105 return [self decodeData: (uint8_t *)inputImage.buffer.bytes size: inputImage.buffer.length timeStamp: inputImage.timeStamp];
106}
107
108- (NSInteger)decodeData:(const uint8_t *)data
109 size:(size_t)size
110 timeStamp:(uint32_t)timeStamp {
111
112 if (_error != noErr) {
113 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Last frame decode failed.";
114 _error = noErr;
115 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
116 }
117
118 rtc::ScopedCFTypeRef<CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef> inputFormat =
119 rtc::ScopedCF(webrtc::CreateVideoFormatDescription(data, size));
120 if (inputFormat) {
121 // Check if the video format has changed, and reinitialize decoder if
122 // needed.
123 if (!CMFormatDescriptionEqual(inputFormat.get(), _videoFormat)) {
124 [self setVideoFormat:inputFormat.get()];
125 int resetDecompressionSessionError = [self resetDecompressionSession];
126 if (resetDecompressionSessionError != WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
127 return resetDecompressionSessionError;
128 }
129 }
130 }
131 if (!_videoFormat) {
132 // We received a frame but we don't have format information so we can't
133 // decode it.
134 // This can happen after backgrounding. We need to wait for the next
135 // sps/pps before we can resume so we request a keyframe by returning an
136 // error.
137 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Missing video format. Frame with sps/pps required.";
138 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
139 }
140 CMSampleBufferRef sampleBuffer = nullptr;
141 if (!webrtc::H264AnnexBBufferToCMSampleBuffer(data,
142 size,
143 _videoFormat,
144 &sampleBuffer,
145 _memoryPool)) {
146 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
147 }
148 RTC_DCHECK(sampleBuffer);
149 VTDecodeFrameFlags decodeFlags = kVTDecodeFrame_EnableAsynchronousDecompression;
150 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameDecodeParams> frameDecodeParams;
151 frameDecodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameDecodeParams(_callback, timeStamp));
152 OSStatus status = VTDecompressionSessionDecodeFrame(
153 _decompressionSession, sampleBuffer, decodeFlags, frameDecodeParams.release(), nullptr);
154#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
155 // Re-initialize the decoder if we have an invalid session while the app is
156 // active or decoder malfunctions and retry the decode request.
157 if ((status == kVTInvalidSessionErr || status == kVTVideoDecoderMalfunctionErr) &&
158 [self resetDecompressionSession] == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
159 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Failed to decode frame with code: " << status
160 << " retrying decode after decompression session reset";
161 frameDecodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameDecodeParams(_callback, timeStamp));
162 status = VTDecompressionSessionDecodeFrame(
163 _decompressionSession, sampleBuffer, decodeFlags, frameDecodeParams.release(), nullptr);
164 }
165#endif
166 CFRelease(sampleBuffer);
167 if (status != noErr) {
168 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to decode frame with code: " << status;
169 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
170 }
171 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
172}
173
174- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoDecoderCallback)callback {
175 _callback = callback;
176}
177
178- (void)setError:(OSStatus)error {
179 _error = error;
180}
181
182- (NSInteger)releaseDecoder {
183 // Need to invalidate the session so that callbacks no longer occur and it
184 // is safe to null out the callback.
185 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
186 [self setVideoFormat:nullptr];
187 _callback = nullptr;
188 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
189}
190
191#pragma mark - Private
192
193- (int)resetDecompressionSession {
194 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
195
196 // Need to wait for the first SPS to initialize decoder.
197 if (!_videoFormat) {
198 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
199 }
200
201 // Set keys for OpenGL and IOSurface compatibilty, which makes the encoder
202 // create pixel buffers with GPU backed memory. The intent here is to pass
203 // the pixel buffers directly so we avoid a texture upload later during
204 // rendering. This currently is moot because we are converting back to an
205 // I420 frame after decode, but eventually we will be able to plumb
206 // CVPixelBuffers directly to the renderer.
207 // TODO(tkchin): Maybe only set OpenGL/IOSurface keys if we know that that
208 // we can pass CVPixelBuffers as native handles in decoder output.
209 static size_t const attributesSize = 3;
210 CFTypeRef keys[attributesSize] = {
211#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) || defined(WEBRTC_MAC_CATALYST)
212 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLCompatibilityKey,
213#elif defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
214 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLESCompatibilityKey,
215#endif
216 kCVPixelBufferIOSurfacePropertiesKey,
217 kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey
218 };
219 CFDictionaryRef ioSurfaceValue = CreateCFTypeDictionary(nullptr, nullptr, 0);
220 int64_t nv12type = kCVPixelFormatType_420YpCbCr8BiPlanarFullRange;
221 CFNumberRef pixelFormat = CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberLongType, &nv12type);
222 CFTypeRef values[attributesSize] = {kCFBooleanTrue, ioSurfaceValue, pixelFormat};
223 CFDictionaryRef attributes = CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, attributesSize);
224 if (ioSurfaceValue) {
225 CFRelease(ioSurfaceValue);
226 ioSurfaceValue = nullptr;
227 }
228 if (pixelFormat) {
229 CFRelease(pixelFormat);
230 pixelFormat = nullptr;
231 }
232 VTDecompressionOutputCallbackRecord record = {
233 decompressionOutputCallback, (__bridge void *)self,
234 };
235 OSStatus status = VTDecompressionSessionCreate(
236 nullptr, _videoFormat, nullptr, attributes, &record, &_decompressionSession);
237 CFRelease(attributes);
238 if (status != noErr) {
239 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create decompression session: " << status;
240 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
241 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
242 }
243 [self configureDecompressionSession];
244
245 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
246}
247
248- (void)configureDecompressionSession {
249 RTC_DCHECK(_decompressionSession);
250#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
251 VTSessionSetProperty(_decompressionSession, kVTDecompressionPropertyKey_RealTime, kCFBooleanTrue);
252#endif
253}
254
255- (void)destroyDecompressionSession {
256 if (_decompressionSession) {
257#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
258 VTDecompressionSessionWaitForAsynchronousFrames(_decompressionSession);
259#else
260#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
261 if ([UIDevice isIOS11OrLater]) {
262 VTDecompressionSessionWaitForAsynchronousFrames(_decompressionSession);
263 }
264#endif
265#endif
266 VTDecompressionSessionInvalidate(_decompressionSession);
267 CFRelease(_decompressionSession);
268 _decompressionSession = nullptr;
269 }
270}
271
272- (void)setVideoFormat:(CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef)videoFormat {
273 if (_videoFormat == videoFormat) {
274 return;
275 }
276 if (_videoFormat) {
277 CFRelease(_videoFormat);
278 }
279 _videoFormat = videoFormat;
280 if (_videoFormat) {
281 CFRetain(_videoFormat);
282 }
283}
284
285- (NSString *)implementationName {
286 return @"VideoToolbox";
287}
